caption: A lovely little square, surrounded by beautiful trees and buildings, and a nice respite from much more touristy areas of Paris. There are so many directions to head off into, and a surprise at every turn.  I was in the area to meet up with other people, and can honestly say that I enjoyed my time spent waiting between flower markets, old cathedrals, and a historic hospital.
Beautiful bird and flower market. Nice place to wonder round after seeing the Norte Dame. Less busy and crowded than the other side of the river.

Notre Dame is an architectural wonder. So is Palais de Justice. It is a nice walk around these monuments and riverside. There is  also March√© aux fleurs nearby which has beautiful plants and flowers to shop.
Absolutely love looking around this place. I wish I was able to take some plants home with me back in the state side. Purchased some dried lavenders and French soaps here as well.
If you like waiting in line for 3 hours in the winter rain for your scheduled appointment at the Prefecture, then this is the Place for you....
